text: goal SecAct infer secreted proteins’ activity RNA-seq data, including bulk, single-cell, spatial data. Secreted proteins tumor microenvironment mediate intercellular interaction among malignant, stromal, immune cells, thereby influencing every stage tumorigenic cascades. Currently, researchers investigating oncogenic role secreted proteins conventional molecular experiments high-throughput techniques like mass spectrometry sequencing. However, former limited studying secreted proteins per study, latter loses spatial position information cells molecules. , propose innovative analytical platform leverages spatial transcriptomics, emerging technology enabling comprehensive mapping gene expression spatial information intact tumor tissue, spatially explore activity function secreted proteins tumor microenvironment.
install SecAct, recommend using devtools: user can install SecAct source code. Click download .
code: # install.packages("devtools") devtools::install_github("data2intelligence/SecAct") # install SecAct in the R environment. install.packages("Path_to_the_source_code", repos = NULL, type="source")

library(SecAct)  Yfile <- file.path(system.file(package = "SecAct"), "extdata/IFNG_GSE100093.diff") Y <- read.table(Yfile,sep="\t",check.names=F)  res <- SecAct.inference(Y, lambda=10000, nrand=1000)  names(res) ## "beta"   "se"     "zscore" "pvalue"  head(res$beta[,1:2]) ##           IFNG.15d.AMG811.Lesional.180.mg IFNG.15d.Placebo.Lesional.0.mg ## Activin A                   -0.0054571949                   -0.002227756 ## BDNF                        -0.0165308969                   -0.003590268 ## BMP2                        -0.0215501262                    0.019876194 ## BMP4                         0.0039773755                    0.003459698 ## BMP6                         0.0004974797                    0.025879907 ## CD40L                       -0.0051185785                    0.001073442  head(res$zscore[,1:2]) ##           IFNG.15d.AMG811.Lesional.180.mg IFNG.15d.Placebo.Lesional.0.mg ## Activin A                      -1.2489955                     -0.5632170 ## BDNF                           -3.7953628                     -0.7830596 ## BMP2                           -4.9343815                      4.4209498 ## BMP4                            0.9777525                      0.8402344 ## BMP6                            0.1167711                      5.7487538 ## CD40L                          -1.2868588                      0.3233309

library(Seurat) library(SeuratData)  InstallData("pbmc3k") data("pbmc3k") pbmc <- UpdateSeuratObject(pbmc3k)   pbmc[["percent.mt"]] <- PercentageFeatureSet(pbmc, pattern = "^MT-") pbmc <- subset(pbmc, subset = nFeature_RNA > 200 & nFeature_RNA < 2500 & percent.mt < 5) pbmc <- NormalizeData(pbmc, normalization.method = "LogNormalize", scale.factor = 10000)  pbmc <- FindVariableFeatures(pbmc, nfeatures = 2000) all.genes <- rownames(pbmc) pbmc <- ScaleData(pbmc, features = all.genes)  pbmc <- RunPCA(pbmc, features = VariableFeatures(object = pbmc)) pbmc <- FindNeighbors(pbmc, dims = 1:10) pbmc <- FindClusters(pbmc, resolution = 0.5) pbmc <- RunUMAP(pbmc, dims = 1:10)  new.cluster.ids <- c("Naive CD4 T", "CD14+ Mono", "Memory CD4 T", "B", "CD8 T", "FCGR3A+ Mono","NK", "DC", "Platelet") names(new.cluster.ids) <- levels(pbmc) pbmc <- RenameIdents(pbmc, new.cluster.ids)   library(SecAct) pbmc <- SecAct.inference(pbmc, lambda=10000, nrand=10)   p1 <- DimPlot(pbmc, reduction = "umap", label = TRUE, pt.size = 0.5) + NoLegend() p2 <- FeaturePlot(pbmc, features = "SecAct_GCSF", cols = c("blue","white","red"), pt.size = 0.5)  library(patchwork) p1|p2

what: Read ST data to an SpaCET object
title: Infer secreted protein activity in spatial transcriptomics data
text: First, download ST data GSE225690. dataset includes two endometrial cancer patients treated anti-Netrin-1 (NTN1) compound. Netrin-1 secreted glycoprotein plays critical roles angiogenesis cell survival, blocking NTN1 inhibits tumor growth. data folder, 01_039_C1d1 01_039_C3d1 represent pre- -treatment tumor samples Patient 01_039, respectively. read ST data R, user can create SpaCET object using create.SpaCET.object.10X.
code: library(SpaCET)  # set the path to the download folder. dataPath <- "/Users/rub2/Downloads/GSE225690_RAW/"  # load ST data to create an SpaCET object. # read on-treatment sample visiumPath <- paste0(dataPath,"01_039_C3d1/outs/") SpaCET_obj_on <- create.SpaCET.object.10X(visiumPath = visiumPath) SpaCET_obj_on <- SpaCET.quality.control(SpaCET_obj_on)  # read pre-treatment sample visiumPath <- paste0(dataPath,"01_039_C1d1/outs/") SpaCET_obj_pre <- create.SpaCET.object.10X(visiumPath = visiumPath) SpaCET_obj_pre <- SpaCET.quality.control(SpaCET_obj_pre)

title: Infer secreted protein activity in spatial transcriptomics data
text: loading ST data, user can run SecAct.inference infer activities 1000 secreted proteins across spot. note, recommend user set parameter Ycontrol include control (background) current ST sample. example, analyze -treatment sample, pre-treatment sample can set control. SecAct normalize expression values gene -treatment sample -spot mean pre-treatment sample. analyzing pre-treatment sample, control sample unavailable. can just set Ycontrol NULL. SecAct normalize expression values gene pre-treatment sample zero mean across spots. words, SecAct regards ST sample control sample.
code: library(SecAct)  # calculate secreted protein activity for the on-treatment sample SpaCET_obj_on <- SecAct.inference(Y = SpaCET_obj_on, Ycontrol = SpaCET_obj_pre)  # calculate secreted protein activity for the pre-treatment sample SpaCET_obj_pre <- SecAct.inference(Y = SpaCET_obj_pre, Ycontrol = NULL)  # show the activity value SpaCET_obj_on@results$SecAct_res$zscore[1:13,1:6] SpaCET_obj_pre@results$SecAct_res$zscore[1:13,1:6]

title: Infer secreted protein activity in spatial transcriptomics data
text: provide SpaCET.visualize.spatialFeature present spatial distribution cell types.   Since cell types relatively low abundance, user can get better vision setting sameScaleForFraction = FALSE. addition, can open interactive visualization panel setting interactive=TRUE browse deconvolution results.
code: # show the spatial distribution of malignant cells and macrophages. SpaCET.visualize.spatialFeature(   SpaCET_obj,    spatialType = "CellFraction",    spatialFeatures=c("Malignant","Macrophage") ) # show the spatial distribution of all cell types. SpaCET.visualize.spatialFeature(   SpaCET_obj,    spatialType = "CellFraction",    spatialFeatures="All",    sameScaleForFraction = TRUE,   pointSize = 0.1,    nrow=5 ) SpaCET.visualize.spatialFeature(SpaCET_obj,interactive=TRUE)

title: Infer secreted protein activity in spatial transcriptomics data
text: decomposing cell fractions, SpaCET can infer intercellular interactions based cell colocalization ligand-receptor coexpression. Linear correlations cell fraction cell types computed across ST spots evaluate cell-type colocalization. High positive correlations indicate cell-type pairs tend colocalize together. infer physical interactions, SpaCET tests co-expression ligand receptor genes within ST spot co-localized cell-type pairs.

title: Infer secreted protein activity in spatial transcriptomics data
text: SpaCET provides SpaCET.CCI.colocalization SpaCET.visualize.colocalization compute visualize co-localized cell-type pairs.
code: # calculate the cell-cell colocalization. SpaCET_obj <- SpaCET.CCI.colocalization(SpaCET_obj)  # visualize the cell-cell colocalization. SpaCET.visualize.colocalization(SpaCET_obj)

title: Secreted Signaling Activity Inference
text: SecAct R package desighed inferring intercellular activity secreted proteins tumors gene expression profiles. Users can input multiple modalities expression data, including bulk, single-cell, spatial transcriptomics. outputs 1248 secreted protein activities sample, individual cell, ST spot, respectively. input data spatial transcriptomics, SecAct additionally calculates secreted signaling velocity spatial spot. velocity direction starts source cell producing secreted protein moves sink cells receiving secreted protein signal. velocity magnitude represents product secreted protein-coding gene expression source cells signaling activities sink cells.
